A bone marrow awareness day, internationally.&#13;
On that specific day the bone marrow issue, will be on the rado, Tv, etc.&#13;
Work places will be approached inorder to locate potential donors.

campaign_super_hero_s_genes_are_in_your_.description:
The campaign attains to show that everyone can be a super hero. It introduces the marrow concept in two ways: bone marrow donations as the final purpose of the campaign, and marrow in a literary sense of 'it is already inside you and you can be a hero'. &#13;
&#13;
Although this is just a funny concept to introduce the project, I believe the purpose of the campaign must be to inform about the marrow donation process and to motivate by showing how easy and real is to become a hero and save a life.

i_like_bone_marrow_donation_do_you.description:
Be it 15 or 50 years old, every person today accesses Facebook atleast once a day. Concept is to start a campaign on Facebook which spreads awareness on the myths and facts about bone marrow donation&#13;
&#13;
This campaign can also give details about bone marrow donation centers and camps.&#13;
&#13;
Concept is not only to show how important bone marrow donation is but also how Cool it is!&#13;

learning_from_coca_cola.description:
What we can learn from the success of Coca Cola applied to engaging bone marrow donation. The keys are:&#13;
1- Real time data  2- Using local entrepreneurial talents  3- Marketing Campaign&#13;
&#13;
&#13;

use_an_international_donor_day_to_kickst.description:
The most important aspects of my plan are:&#13;
	1) Make registration free and easy with an annual International Marrow Donor Day&#13;
	2) Make it normal, expected and a cause for pride to be in the registry&#13;
	3) Once the majority are in the database, continually add younger generations

giving_back_patients_and_donors_as_resou.description:
Patient and donor stories are compelling and real.  Along with demystifying the process, the "does it hurt" fear, the medical side of the equation, partnering with former patients  could help.  It always helps me to talk to other people who have had similar experiences.&#13;
&#13;
When I share my bone marrow transplant experience, it changes everything.  People want to help if they understand and know how.  Medical professionals love to hear how they've affected patient's lives in a positive way. So do other people.&#13;
&#13;
Seeing yourself in the picture, as a helper and resource, is a good feeling.  &#13;
&#13;
Developing a series of "on-the-spot thank-you's" and email messages is a good idea.  "Here is a message from...she/he wants to thank-you on behalf of all transplant patients around the world".&#13;
&#13;
I would be willing to participate in something like this, I'm always looking for a way to give back.&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
&#13;

you_got_a_mama.description:
A campaign aimed at activating the community of women in the developing world through the common sentiment of being a mother, and the feelings that that entails.  &#13;
&#13;
Inspired by direct selling initiatives of global companies such as Avon or Natura, this campaign aims to cross feelings of apprehension, misunderstanding, fear, and reluctance that  the developing world population may have about becoming a donor through peer-to-peer dialogue.&#13;

_become_a_life_saver_social_bone_marrow_.description:
To build up a personal and emotional relationship between the actual donor and the patients in need, a social online network, where people become real, with real faces, stories and feelings, could be provided.&#13;
Real life-savers become featured members and earn lifer saver credits and post and amplify their story, together with the patient. People get educated through the network, become "bone marrow experts" and go out to tell thousands of stories to the people all over the world.&#13;
&#13;

drawing_inspiration_from_toms_shoes.description:
The success of TOMS Shoes is inspiring two main reasons:&#13;
1) TOMS has brought attention to the unlikely cause of soil-transmitted diseases through their one-for-one donation model. &#13;
2) TOMS "Day Without Shoes" event engages empathic participants.  &#13;

how_does_it_really_feel_to_donate_bone_m.description:
As many have pointed out, one of the greatest deterrents to bone marrow donation is the fear of the pain the procedure causes. As I have also learned (I'll admit I also had this perception before reading more about bone marrow donation) that this is not necessarily true. I also know that perceptions are hard to break with words, actions speak louder.&#13;
&#13;
So in order to demonstrate what it feels like to donate marrow - how about a physical analogy to give people and idea of the actual pain threshold. &#13;

beyond_the_familiar_spreading_the_word_g.description:
